      "content": "---\n**MEMORANDUM**\n\nTo: [Company Name] Compliance Team  \nFrom: [Your Name]  \nDate: [Current Date]  \nSubject: KYC Compliance Memo for New Client Onboarding Process\n\n---\n\n**Introduction**\n\nThis memo outlines the comprehensive Know Your Customer (KYC) compliance procedures to ensure adherence to regulatory standards and legal requirements during the onboarding process of new clients. The following steps and documentation are designed to meet the stringent guidelines set forth by regulatory authorities, thereby ensuring a smooth and compliant onboarding experience.\n\n**1. Customer Identification Program (CIP)**\n- Collect and verify the following personal information:\n  - Full name\n  - Date of birth\n  - Address\n  - Nationality\n  - Tax identification number (TIN)\n  - Proof of identity (e.g., government-issued ID)\n  - Proof of address (e.g., utility bill, bank statement)\n- Conduct enhanced due diligence (EDD) for high-risk clients, including:\n  - Source of funds\n  - Beneficial ownership information\n  - Transaction history\n\n**2. Risk Assessment**\n- Perform a risk assessment based on the client's profile, transaction patterns, and geographic location.\n- Classify clients into risk categories (low, medium,",
